headline: Molina Healthcare (MOH): Assessing Valuation After Lowered 2025 Outlook and Medical Cost Concerns
summary: If you’re watching Molina Healthcare (MOH) right now and wondering what just happened, you’re not alone. The stock bounced back 2.5% after a steep sell-off triggered by its second-quarter 2025 earnings report. That report showed a 6.5% year-over-year drop in adjusted earnings per share, and management cut its full-year outlook, blaming heavier medical costs. With a law firm launching an investor investigation and Wall Street shifting to a “Hold” consensus, it is clear this is not just routine...
